# Record Open Edit Mode Propagation

For any block/component that opens records (via `openRecordModal` or `openRecord`), preserve interface edit mode end-to-end.

## Required

- Accept `interfaceMode?: "view" | "edit"` in new block wrappers and core components.
- Forward `interfaceMode` through wrapper -> core -> record-open handler props.
- Pass `interfaceMode` into `openRecordModal({ interfaceMode })` and `openRecord(..., interfaceMode, ...)`.
- Default to `"view"` only as a fallback when `interfaceMode` is truly unavailable; never hardcode `"view"` at call sites when the current mode exists.

## Forbidden

- Ignoring/destructuring away `interfaceMode` (e.g. `interfaceMode: _interfaceMode`).
- Hardcoded `interfaceMode: "view"` in record-open calls for blocks that can run in edit mode.

## Quick check before merge

- In page edit mode, opening a record from the block opens an editable record surface.
- In view mode, behavior remains unchanged.
